{
  "texts": [
    "For example, if they want to get information about the synthesis method of a certain material, they search based on some keywords in a paper search engine and get information retrieval results (a set of papers).",
    "Then, valid papers (papers that are likely to contain the necessary information) are selected based on information such as title, abstract, author, and journal.",
    "Next, they can read the main text of the paper, locate paragraphs that may contain the desired information (e.g., synthesis), and organize the information at the sentence or word level.",
    "Here, the process of selecting papers or finding paragraphs can be conducted through a text classification model, while the process of recognising, extracting, and organising information can be done through an information extraction model.",
    "Therefore, this study mainly deals with how text classification and information extraction can be performed through LLMs."
  ]
}